1
00:00:36,079 --> 00:00:36,759
Come up.

2
00:00:37,560 --> 00:00:38,119
Old Chen!

3
00:00:38,119 --> 00:00:38,920
Chen Youxi!

4
00:00:47,359 --> 00:00:47,960
Old Chen!

5
00:00:48,560 --> 00:00:49,200
Are you okay?

6
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:50,799
Wake up.

7
00:00:53,600 --> 00:00:54,759
Let's see what's going on.

8
00:00:55,159 --> 00:00:56,880
Talk about being lucky and blessed.

9
00:00:57,920 --> 00:00:58,479
I need to take a look.

10
00:00:58,479 --> 00:00:59,399
I think...

11
00:00:59,600 --> 00:01:01,920
It must be that big eye on Old Chen's back.

12
00:01:01,920 --> 00:01:03,119
It's too bizarre.

13
00:01:03,159 --> 00:01:04,519
They don't dare mess with him.

14
00:01:05,439 --> 00:01:06,280
Makes sense.

15
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:08,400
Then let's do this from now on.

16
00:01:08,519 --> 00:01:10,280
Whenever we run into snakes, bugs, rats, or ants,

17
00:01:10,439 --> 00:01:11,799
Old Chen, you just take off your clothes,

18
00:01:11,799 --> 00:01:12,599
lie down right there,

19
00:01:12,719 --> 00:01:13,799
and we'll be saved.

20
00:01:13,799 --> 00:01:14,519
Get lost.

21
00:01:15,040 --> 00:01:16,000
That won't do.

22
00:01:16,280 --> 00:01:16,879
If we run into danger

23
00:01:16,879 --> 00:01:18,079
and push Old Chen forward,

24
00:01:18,079 --> 00:01:19,760
Staff Officer He won't be happy about it.

25
00:01:20,680 --> 00:01:21,879
Let's be serious.

26
00:01:22,200 --> 00:01:24,000
I guess we're almost at the Mountain God Temple.

27
00:01:24,359 --> 00:01:26,640
This line should be called the Bug-Repelling Path.

28
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:29,040
To ensure the Fengshui lasts for thousands of years,

29
00:01:29,239 --> 00:01:30,920
the Mountain God Temple cannot suffer any damage.

30
00:01:30,920 --> 00:01:32,920
Wooden structures are most afraid of bug infestations.

31
00:01:33,400 --> 00:01:35,079
So the King of Dian must have, near the ancient tomb,

32
00:01:35,079 --> 00:01:37,159
buried a lot of long-lasting bug-repelling secret medicine.

33
00:01:37,840 --> 00:01:38,640
This method

34
00:01:38,640 --> 00:01:40,760
is very common in Han Dynasty imperial tombs.

35
00:01:41,319 --> 00:01:42,359
The simplest one

36
00:01:42,359 --> 00:01:43,920
is burying sulfur and mercury.

37
00:01:43,920 --> 00:01:44,599
Right.

38
00:01:44,719 --> 00:01:46,760
Combined with plants like Mamasen, Xunhuangji,

39
00:01:46,799 --> 00:01:48,920
and Lanputi to balance them out,

40
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:50,040
their properties counteract each other.

41
00:01:50,040 --> 00:01:50,840
Buried in the ground,

42
00:01:50,840 --> 00:01:52,359
they won't completely evaporate for thousands of years.

43
00:01:53,439 --> 00:01:55,280
It seems the Tomb of the King of Dian is nearby.

44
00:01:55,280 --> 00:01:55,959
That's right.

45
00:01:56,519 --> 00:01:58,920
Let's walk straight up along this Bug-Repelling Path.

46
00:01:58,920 --> 00:02:00,040
After three Bug-Repelling Paths,

47
00:02:00,040 --> 00:02:01,400
there are nine winding turns facing the mountain shore.

48
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:02,760
The final turn is right ahead.

49
00:02:02,760 --> 00:02:04,000
Bye-bye, mastiffs.

50
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:05,000
Blister beetles.

51
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:05,959
I know, I know.

52
00:02:06,079 --> 00:02:07,120
It's a term of endearment.

53
00:02:14,319 --> 00:02:17,120
This Fengshui stuff is so amazing.

54
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:18,360
Fish can't leave the water,

55
00:02:18,680 --> 00:02:19,800
melons can't leave the vine,

56
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:22,759
and dragon-hunting relies on the secret art of geomancy.

57
00:02:23,319 --> 00:02:24,400
The secret art of geomancy?

58
00:02:25,080 --> 00:02:26,719
Is that your textbook?

59
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:27,960
You could say that.

60
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:30,680
Then I'll borrow it from the library to read later.

61
00:02:30,680 --> 00:02:31,439
Comrades,

62
00:02:32,039 --> 00:02:32,919
we're here.

63
00:02:35,919 --> 00:02:37,960
Is this the big toad we're looking for?

64
00:02:37,960 --> 00:02:39,759
Why doesn't it look like a toad at all?

65
00:02:39,759 --> 00:02:41,520
You don't look like a Pixiu either, do you?

66
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:43,400
It's a symbol.

67
00:02:44,240 --> 00:02:45,039
A symbol.

68
00:02:51,439 --> 00:02:52,240
Let's go.

69
00:03:07,400 --> 00:03:09,319
Why are these vines so long?

70
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:12,360
Plenty of sunlight and heavy rainfall.

71
00:03:12,599 --> 00:03:13,879
They eat a lot, so they grow long.

72
00:03:13,879 --> 00:03:15,159
You don't even know this logic?

73
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:16,960
Even if it has plenty of nutrients,

74
00:03:17,520 --> 00:03:19,360
it shouldn't exceed a certain threshold.

75
00:03:21,280 --> 00:03:22,960
Listen, what's that sound?

76
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:29,439
Look at this.

77
00:03:29,439 --> 00:03:30,960
It's... it's moving! It's moving!

78
00:03:31,639 --> 00:03:32,599
Here, here! It's moving!

79
00:03:33,159 --> 00:03:33,879
It's still moving!

80
00:03:33,879 --> 00:03:36,199
Could it be those mastiffs chasing us again?

81
00:03:38,319 --> 00:03:39,520
It's moving. Snakes?

82
00:03:39,639 --> 00:03:40,280
Snakes?

83
00:03:40,560 --> 00:03:41,280
A whole swarm.

84
00:03:42,120 --> 00:03:42,960
So many of them.

85
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:44,520
Darn it, a swarm of snakes is coming.

86
00:03:46,319 --> 00:03:46,960
Old Lu!

87
00:03:47,120 --> 00:03:47,680
Old Lu!

88
00:03:57,719 --> 00:03:59,080
Looks like it wasn't just that one vine.

89
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:07,360
Everyone, be careful!

90
00:04:10,719 --> 00:04:11,800
Everyone, hurry up and go!

91
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:13,159
Hurry!

92
00:04:23,199 --> 00:04:23,800
Go!

93
00:04:24,399 --> 00:04:25,000
Hurry!

94
00:04:27,480 --> 00:04:28,720
Fatty, Shutong,

95
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:30,120
look after Old Lu and Dawei!

96
00:04:31,120 --> 00:04:32,720
Let's see just how long you are.

97
00:04:33,639 --> 00:04:34,439
Fatty!

98
00:04:34,439 --> 00:04:35,680
Count how many there are in total.

99
00:04:35,680 --> 00:04:36,360
Got it.

100
00:04:37,279 --> 00:04:37,800
One.

101
00:04:39,079 --> 00:04:39,560
Two.

102
00:04:52,279 --> 00:04:53,879
What number was I on?

103
00:05:08,560 --> 00:05:09,360
Three.

104
00:05:23,079 --> 00:05:23,839
Shutong!

105
00:05:50,079 --> 00:05:50,879
Four.

106
00:06:00,839 --> 00:06:01,800
Where's the other one?

107
00:06:20,160 --> 00:06:20,959
Fatty

108
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:24,319
Did you count them clearly? How many vines?

109
00:06:24,480 --> 00:06:25,279
I counted them clearly.

110
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:27,199
Six... six vines.

111
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:29,600
Fatty.

112
00:06:30,160 --> 00:06:30,959
Five vines.

113
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:32,360
I mean...

114
00:06:32,639 --> 00:06:34,360
Would the sixth one even dare to come?

115
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:36,959
These vines...

116
00:06:37,560 --> 00:06:40,120
Are they like pitcher plants?

117
00:06:41,120 --> 00:06:42,399
Do they devour living things?

118
00:06:42,519 --> 00:06:44,720
In the tropical rainforests of Panama,

119
00:06:45,120 --> 00:06:46,439
there grows a man-eating vine.

120
00:06:46,920 --> 00:06:47,720
It's said that

121
00:06:48,319 --> 00:06:49,800
once you touch its vines,

122
00:06:49,879 --> 00:06:51,120
they act like a python,

123
00:06:51,120 --> 00:06:52,639
tightly wrapping around a person.

124
00:06:52,879 --> 00:06:53,600
Right.

125
00:06:54,519 --> 00:06:56,040
In the forests of Brazil,

126
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:59,040
there's a shrub called Yanipinda.

127
00:06:59,399 --> 00:07:00,839
It's covered in hooked thorns.

128
00:07:00,839 --> 00:07:01,720
Once touched,

129
00:07:01,759 --> 00:07:03,560
these thorns will swarm over,

130
00:07:03,639 --> 00:07:06,360
tightly entangling and piercing humans or animals.

131
00:07:06,720 --> 00:07:09,800
Some plants are very sensitive to light, sound,

132
00:07:10,120 --> 00:07:11,319
and touch.

133
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:12,759
Don't touch it anymore.

134
00:07:12,759 --> 00:07:13,759
Just talking about it is enough.

135
00:07:13,759 --> 00:07:15,560
The flora and fauna here are really strange.

136
00:07:16,639 --> 00:07:18,160
The miasma water stingers we met before,

137
00:07:18,920 --> 00:07:20,519
and now these vines.

138
00:07:20,959 --> 00:07:21,680
Exactly.

139
00:07:21,959 --> 00:07:22,959
So I think

140
00:07:23,120 --> 00:07:24,360
there might have really been

141
00:07:24,360 --> 00:07:25,759
severe crustal movements here.

142
00:07:25,920 --> 00:07:26,959
The plants and animals here,

143
00:07:26,959 --> 00:07:28,240
in order to survive better,

144
00:07:28,240 --> 00:07:30,160
underwent such abnormal evolution.

145
00:07:30,199 --> 00:07:31,600
Abnormal evolution.

146
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:32,240
Right.

147
00:07:32,240 --> 00:07:33,879
Didn't we run into that

148
00:07:34,040 --> 00:07:35,439
Ghost-faced Soul-eating Spider before?

149
00:07:35,560 --> 00:07:37,120
Didn't it also evolve and evolve,

150
00:07:37,120 --> 00:07:39,279
until it turned into that messy thing?

151
00:07:39,279 --> 00:07:40,519
And that Blue-scaled Flood Dragon King,

152
00:07:40,519 --> 00:07:41,600
that huge thing,

153
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:43,319
it bumped our boat so hard,

154
00:07:43,319 --> 00:07:44,720
we almost fell into the river.

155
00:07:45,959 --> 00:07:47,079
Hearing you guys talk

156
00:07:47,360 --> 00:07:48,279
reminds me of

157
00:07:48,279 --> 00:07:50,360
the rats in the ruins of Chernobyl.

158
00:07:50,480 --> 00:07:53,079
They say some are as big as piglets.

159
00:07:53,439 --> 00:07:55,160
The rats in the ruins of Chernobyl

160
00:07:55,759 --> 00:07:57,199
were caused by strong radiation, right?

161
00:07:57,680 --> 00:07:58,800
The places you've walked through,

162
00:07:58,800 --> 00:08:00,560
did they also have some highly radioactive materials?

163
00:08:01,040 --> 00:08:02,759
If you're talking about radioactive materials,

164
00:08:02,759 --> 00:08:03,759
I have to tell you about it.

165
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:04,680
Do you know?

166
00:08:11,120 --> 00:08:13,120
This... the things that happened before,

167
00:08:13,120 --> 00:08:14,560
let's... let's not talk about them.

168
00:08:14,920 --> 00:08:16,319
It's all ancient history.

169
00:08:16,399 --> 00:08:17,920
Let's talk about what's happening now.

170
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:19,319
What thing turned into what thing,

171
00:08:19,319 --> 00:08:20,240
and how it changed,

172
00:08:20,240 --> 00:08:22,000
it's a mess, who can say for sure?

173
00:08:23,240 --> 00:08:24,399
Take this back.

174
00:08:24,680 --> 00:08:26,360
Later, dig a pot of soil and take a scoop of water.

175
00:08:26,959 --> 00:08:28,600
Go back to your lab and study it slowly.

176
00:08:31,399 --> 00:08:32,039
I'm exhausted.

177
00:08:37,440 --> 00:08:39,919
You see, just this small facade,

178
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:41,679
you can tell from this

179
00:08:41,799 --> 00:08:43,519
that old King of Dian must be very stingy.

180
00:08:43,799 --> 00:08:45,039
This mountain god temple should be

181
00:08:45,039 --> 00:08:46,720
a Xieshan-style large wooden frame structure.

182
00:08:46,720 --> 00:08:48,159
Divided into front and back courtyards.

183
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:49,360
What we are seeing here

184
00:08:49,480 --> 00:08:50,799
should just be the facade.

185
00:08:51,159 --> 00:08:52,720
Look at this timber, it's completely rotten,

186
00:08:52,720 --> 00:08:53,759
but it still hasn't collapsed.

187
00:08:53,759 --> 00:08:55,200
It's quite a miracle.

188
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:57,840
Maybe it's exactly because this is the focal point of the water dragon vein,

189
00:08:57,840 --> 00:08:59,399
which is quite good at gathering wind and energy,

190
00:08:59,759 --> 00:09:01,759
that this general framework has been preserved.

191
00:09:09,720 --> 00:09:10,919
There's a big gourd here.

192
00:09:10,919 --> 00:09:11,919
Come take a look.

193
00:09:12,120 --> 00:09:13,120
What big gourd?

194
00:09:15,080 --> 00:09:15,759
Look.

195
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:19,960
Never heard of a mountain god temple worshipping a gourd.

196
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:20,759
Fatty.

197
00:09:21,279 --> 00:09:21,840
There's a crack here.

198
00:09:21,840 --> 00:09:23,000
See if we can move it.

199
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:23,639
Okay.

200
00:09:28,879 --> 00:09:29,759
Let me try again.

201
00:09:31,039 --> 00:09:31,840
Push hard!

202
00:09:38,240 --> 00:09:39,960
No way, it won't open.

203
00:09:42,240 --> 00:09:43,159
There's probably a mechanism.

204
00:09:47,120 --> 00:09:48,559
You're just tiring me out for nothing!

205
00:09:50,480 --> 00:09:52,480
Next time, can you mention the mechanism first?

206
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:26,759
Didn't you say this is a mountain god temple?

207
00:10:27,480 --> 00:10:28,679
Then where is the mountain god?

208
00:10:28,960 --> 00:10:30,879
The mountain god is sleeping right here.

209
00:10:31,279 --> 00:10:33,000
Why is he lying down here?

210
00:10:33,080 --> 00:10:33,919
Guys, give me a hand.

211
00:10:33,919 --> 00:10:35,960
Let's put the mountain god back in his place.

212
00:10:36,240 --> 00:10:37,919
So he can bless our journey to go smoothly.

213
00:10:37,919 --> 00:10:39,399
And prevent any mishaps.

214
00:10:39,559 --> 00:10:40,000
Come on.

215
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:41,759
I think, for someone like you,

216
00:10:42,120 --> 00:10:44,080
believing and praying for things is unreliable.

217
00:10:44,840 --> 00:10:46,080
If you ask me,

218
00:10:46,279 --> 00:10:47,879
we might as well just let him lie there.

219
00:10:49,759 --> 00:10:51,000
How does the saying go?

220
00:10:51,480 --> 00:10:52,960
Nothing is more delicious than dumplings,

221
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:54,799
and nothing is more comfortable than lying down.

222
00:11:00,080 --> 00:11:02,559
These little imps on the side,

223
00:11:02,639 --> 00:11:04,679
one is holding a fire gourd,

224
00:11:04,840 --> 00:11:06,879
and the other is holding a toad.

225
00:11:06,960 --> 00:11:08,440
What does that mean?

226
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:19,120
I don't know about the rest,

227
00:11:19,120 --> 00:11:20,120
but this gourd,

228
00:11:20,240 --> 00:11:22,039
its pronunciation is similar to "fortune and wealth."

229
00:11:22,039 --> 00:11:24,200
It has a big belly and a small mouth,

230
00:11:24,720 --> 00:11:26,639
specifically designed to suck in gold, silver, and jewels.

231
00:11:26,879 --> 00:11:28,720
And with the mouth facing outward,

232
00:11:28,759 --> 00:11:30,919
it's placed correctly. It attracts wealth.

233
00:11:31,919 --> 00:11:34,120
But in the culture of the Qin and Han dynasties,

234
00:11:34,120 --> 00:11:35,960
gourds were used to hold elixirs and magic potions.

235
00:11:35,960 --> 00:11:37,960
They could increase blessings, bring good luck, and ward off disasters.

236
00:11:38,200 --> 00:11:40,879
They could also absorb evil spirits in the area.

237
00:11:42,279 --> 00:11:43,799
So the mouth of this gourd

238
00:11:44,519 --> 00:11:46,360
should actually be facing inward.

239
00:12:33,960 --> 00:12:34,759
Oh my god.

240
00:12:37,360 --> 00:12:38,279
What is this thing?

241
00:12:38,600 --> 00:12:39,679
A giant toad.

242
00:12:42,440 --> 00:12:43,360
Good lord.

243
00:12:44,840 --> 00:12:46,559
Where did all these giant toads come from?

244
00:12:57,919 --> 00:13:00,200
It really corresponds to the number of the Nine-Bend Meander.

245
00:13:01,120 --> 00:13:01,919
Yes, yes, yes.

246
00:13:02,279 --> 00:13:04,679
I just finished counting. Exactly nine of them.

247
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:22,360
These toads can all move!

248
00:13:23,360 --> 00:13:24,960
Could this be a mechanism?

249
00:13:25,240 --> 00:13:26,679
Otherwise, did you think they were just for show?

250
00:13:26,679 --> 00:13:28,159
Did you think they were your bar snacks?

251
00:13:28,240 --> 00:13:29,320
Did you think they were mountain gods?

252
00:13:30,200 --> 00:13:32,120
Okay, okay, okay. You guys know it all.

253
00:13:32,320 --> 00:13:33,320
You figure it out.

254
00:13:33,320 --> 00:13:34,399
I'm not going to bother anymore.

255
00:13:54,440 --> 00:13:54,840
Since it's

256
00:13:54,840 --> 00:13:57,039
the layout of the Nine-Bend Meander facing the mountain shore,

257
00:13:57,480 --> 00:13:58,360
then let's follow

258
00:13:58,360 --> 00:14:00,279
the feng shui thinking of the ancients.

259
00:14:00,759 --> 00:14:01,919
Nine toads,

260
00:14:02,279 --> 00:14:03,360
nine acupoints.

261
00:14:03,879 --> 00:14:05,679
The first to ninth hexagrams in the I Ching:

262
00:14:06,200 --> 00:14:09,000
Qian, Kun, Zhun,

263
00:14:09,639 --> 00:14:12,360
Meng, Xu, Song,

264
00:14:12,720 --> 00:14:15,519
Shi, Bi, and Xiao Xu.

265
00:14:16,240 --> 00:14:18,120
Then their positions should be

266
00:14:29,759 --> 00:14:30,399
North,

267
00:14:33,240 --> 00:14:33,879
South,

268
00:14:36,879 --> 00:14:37,679
Southwest,

269
00:14:39,080 --> 00:14:39,879
Northwest.

270
00:15:16,120 --> 00:15:16,960
Let's go, let's go.

271
00:15:27,799 --> 00:15:29,159
It really is a giant toad cave.

272
00:15:29,679 --> 00:15:30,759
The mark on the tomb-guarding record

273
00:15:30,759 --> 00:15:32,080
should be pointing right here.

274
00:15:32,080 --> 00:15:32,960
If I'm not mistaken,

275
00:15:32,960 --> 00:15:33,879
inside here should be

276
00:15:33,879 --> 00:15:35,320
the only passage leading to the Ming Pavilion.

277
00:15:37,840 --> 00:15:38,600
I'll take the lead.

278
00:15:38,600 --> 00:15:39,240
Let's go.

279
00:15:39,879 --> 00:15:40,480
Let's go.

